-- Gazprom, Lukoil, Magnit, Novatek May Move: Russian Equity Market Preview
-- Lucian Kim
-- 2010-06-24T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/gazprom-lukoil-magnit-novatek-may-move-russian-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  
 The Micex Index of 30 stocks slipped 0.7 percent to
1,377.97 at the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS
Index fell 1.2 percent to 1,418.42.  
 OAO Gazprom  (GAZP RX): Russia’s largest energy company said
it will end a cut in natural-gas supplies to Belarus once the
country repays a debt. Gazprom slid 0.8 percent to 158.06
rubles.  
 OAO Lukoil  (LKOH RX): Crude oil fell the most in more than
two weeks after U.S. government reports showed an unexpected
gain in supplies and purchases of new homes tumbled. Shares in
Russia’s biggest non-state oil company rose 0.5 percent to
1,695.81 rubles.  
 OAO Magnit  (MGNT RX): Shareholders in Russia’s second-
biggest food retailer will vote on the 2009 dividend at an
annual meeting on June 24. Magnit fell 1 percent to 2,639.55
rubles.  
 OAO Novatek  (NVTK LI): Standard and Poor’s Ratings Services
said it raised its long-term corporate credit rating on Russia’s
second-largest natural-gas producer to BBB- from BB+. Novatek
dropped 2.2 percent to $77.30 in London.  
